<div class=3D"simple-text parbase section">
<div class=3D"simple-text theme--light ">
<h2 class=3D"heading" data-number=3D"3">Mean reversion using Bollinger band=
s</h2>
<p>This strategy utilises the Bollinger band tool with the 20-day SMA place=
d within the middle of the bands. This technique can be used without the Bo=
llinger bands, but using the bands provides some additional benefits. The i=
dea behind this method is that even when we see a highly trending market, t=
he price will often return to mean before pushing back in the direction of =
the trend. As such, the middle Bollinger band (the 20-day SMA) will often b=
e utilised as support or resistance, providing a useful buying and selling =
tool.</p>
<p>The chart below highlights the strategy in action, with the price fallin=
g below the 20-day SMA on the top left, indicating the switch from bullish =
to bearish sentiment. From there on in, the reversion back into the 20-day =
SMA provided a host of profitable selling opportunities.</p>
<p>On this occasion, the upper Bollinger band would have been useful as a t=
ool to place your stop loss above. Alternatively, utilising the prior swing=
 high would have also provided a profitable trading strategy. The dotted ho=
rizontal lines signal where those swing highs are located.</p>
</div></div>
